      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "POWER ROLEX (6) has gone well at his last couple of runs here, most recently when third beaten 2.75 lengths (17.87). Has a win and two places times at this track. Has good early speed and can overcome the tricky draw. Can go on with it. BLUE LEGEND (1) turned in a modest effort most recently when fifth at this track over 300m behind Where's The Luck (17.91) in a Grade 5. Placed at his previous run. Good beginner assisted by the inside draw. Has ability and is one of the better chances. PAW BELLONDA (5) started big odds last time but hit the ground running with a slick early split, giving a sight but fading out of it to finish fourth (17.87) at this track over 300m. Yet to win out of this box but has been in the placings two times from four starts. Cannot be taken lightly. TEQUILA RIPPLE (8) will need to run right up to last start to feature again.",
